genresAdvancedInfo.name: experimental dub
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Experimental dub is a subgenre of dub music that incorporates unconventional sounds and techniques. It often features heavy use of effects such as reverb and delay, as well as experimentation with rhythm and melody. The genre is known for its emphasis on bass and its use of spacey, atmospheric textures.
